annotation.TEXT: Well, let's get off of this creepy Flandre map at least...
DANGER! Energy is very low!
Alright, it's true final boss time, against... Scarlet Bowser! And, right away, he is not fooling around! There are already evil homing bullets flying around from the word "go"!
TWO Bowsers?! When did he fuse with Gemini Man?
I wonder if the game had expected me to move to the center by now.
Also, due to me finishing the previous phase just after taking a hit, my energy is now an unusual amount. (The last hit I took in the previous phase only dealt 17 damage.)
Okay, now let's head to the -END OF THE GAME -!
Oh, no. Am I going to have my first fair and square Game Over here?
Oh, I guess I can jump on him now. So, that's what I'm going to do!
Whoa, I don't believe I've seen this attack before in this hack. But, how do I damage him? Do I wait for him to summon an enemy that I can send back to him?
CAUTION: Energy is starting to get low!
Looks like there's nothing but a pipe here. I guess I'll go down it.
Seriously, that Flandre wing bursting out of Bowser's back is just creepy!
Wah! What the heck?! Did Bowser use Polymerization to fuse with Flandre or something?
Looks like Bowser gets hit if he just simply walks into a stunned Bob-omb, but explosions appear to have no effect.
Go, my Flandre essence blocks, and fill the world with your Flandre essence-ness!
Whoa, what is that thing? That must be the Flandre essence!
Finally got in a hit. That seemed trickier than it should've been.
Umm... 495? (Just a wild guess.)
And now Bowser's tossing shuriken. Yeah, I'm going to take a buttload of hits here.
Alright, it's final boss time, against Bowser himself! So, he's in classic SMB1 mode right now, and we appear to be in an elevator going down.
So, it's basically a cape, but unfortunately, I can't actually fly. All I've got is the cape spin and gliding abilities (just like Super Marina World's cape).
Nuts. It would help if those bullets didn't keep causing the Bob-ombs to turn around before they can reach me.
Yeah, nuts to this. I'm just going to tank hits now.
Oh, man. He's getting intelligent with his jumps!
Actually, this phase doesn't seem nearly as hectic, and I can catch my breath on the left side of the screen. However, it doesn't look like I can attack him from there.
Nuts. I take my first hit, because Bowser decided to crowd me.
Let's find out! (Although you've probably already guessed who it is, based on the level's music, and if not, the subtitle to this episode gives it away anyway.)
Or, maybe I can, if I aim right.
Wow, really? It's narrowing even more?

Okay, so if anybody knows of anything in this hack that can only be reached or accomplished with the Flandre essence, let me know! Also, if there are any other things you guys want me to do in this hack, let me know!
Okay, so now what?
I wonder if that particular number is a Flandre reference, and I also wonder how many total times Mario has defeated Bowser in all of the official Mario games...
Well, until the game gives me a reason to move, this is all I'm going to do!
Haha, wow. I know I'm probably going to have to move eventually, but this just seems so funny right now.
Flandre essence? Oh, man. I definitely gotta check this out!
Zwee!
Looks like I have to hit him directly with Bob-ombs to damage him.
Nothing special up there. (That would've been neat if this level had another exit that I needed the Flandre essence to reach.)
Looks like the extreme lower-left is no longer an option, but I'll try to stay as close to that corner as I can.
Oy. I'm glad that phase is over. I took a ton of damage there. Looks like I can heal up a bit here, but how nasty will this phase be?
The spacing of the words in that level name looks odd. Maybe remove one of the spaces between "OF" and "THE", and add a space before "END" to make it look neater.
Whoa! Now he's tossing shuriken!

Hello, and welcome back to Touhou Mario! Last time, I had worked my way through the stage portion of this level. However, due to how long the video would've been as a whole with the boss fight included (over 20 minutes), and how irritating YouTube's been lately, I decided to split this into two parts.
Insert apostrophe here.
Does this surprise involve Kogasa?
Whoa! Did I... decapitate him?!?! Oh, geez...
Argh. If it weren't for the bullets interfering with the Bob-ombs' movement, I could probably still mount an offensive from back here, but it looks like I'm going to have to get in close.
Okay, now I have to move to dodge some spikes.
Wait... Can I seriously just duck in the lower-left corner and "Icicle Fall Easy" this part?
Oh, my god. That was intense. And I won with only 42 energy left! (Yep, my current HP is the answer to life, the universe, and everything!)
Ow. I hit a fireball. That's okay. I've got a good rhythm going now.
Okay, that phase is done... OMGWTHIT?!
Oh, haha! Wasn't there an episode of Super Mario Bros. Super Show where Bowser was indeed called Count Koopula?
BGM: Boss Z (SMW Boss theme remix)
Capitalize "you".
Push!
And, if you look closely, you'll notice that the Bowser has his eyes open, while the fake one's eyes are closed.
Oh, man. The corridor's getting even narrower, so now I probably should move into the center.
But, for now, I hope you all enjoyed watching me play through Touhou Mario! See ya!
Have you ever known Bowser to give up so easily?
I am going to take this opportunity to heal up before I go to the next level. (And I may as well grab a B card while I'm here.)
Alright, so let's revisit Congratulations! and take a look at what this Flandre essence does!
Hmm... I guess only one of the Bowsers actually takes damage. The other one is invincible.
I think I've completely finished this hack.
Geez. That phase is done, but I can't take much more punishment. So, now what's the deal with this phase?
And now I've got... Flandre's wings. Is this what Bowser was actually using before?
Oh! This must be the fabled switch palace of legend!
BGM: Scarlet Bowser JI (U. N. Owen was her? remix)
Oh, hey there, Bowser. How's it going?
Oh, hey there, Scarlet Bowser. How's it going?
Oh, man. Thanks for the invincibility! (This time it was due to me taking a hit just before the screen transition.)
We'll see about that...
